Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
compare_release(25.10)                                  compare_release(25.10)

Name
       compare_release  -  Compares two different releases and reports all the
       added, deleted, or modified commands, arguments, and global variables

Syntax
       compare_release

       [-help]

       [-out_file <file_name>]

       {-base_version <release_version> | -base_file <file_name>}

       [-target_version <release_version> | -target_file <file_name>]

       Compares two different releases and reports all the added, deleted,  or
       modified commands, arguments, and global variables. It also reports any
       data-type  changes  for  argument  values or globals and any enum value
       changes.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each compare_release parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man compare_release

       -base_file <file_name>
              Specifies the .info file of the older base release.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -base_version <release_version>
              Specifies the older base release,  such  as  16.10-p001_1,  from
              <install>/share/innovus/version_info.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -out_file <file_name>
              Specifie the output report file.

              Default: stdout

              Data_type: string, optional

       -target_file <file_name>
              Specifies the  target release .info file to be compared with the
              older base release .info file.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -target_version <release_version>
              Specifies  the  version, such as 16.20-p002_1, which is compared
              to the older base release. Looks in <install>/share/innovus/ver-
              sion_info for the correct .info file.

              Default: Current version

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              *

                The following command compares two releases by  first  finding
                the  install  directories, and the correct .info files to com-
                pare.

                >which innovus

                /tools/innovus18.11/bin/innovus

                The install directory above is /tools/innovus18.11 (for  exam-
                ples, the 18.1 ISR release).

                Suppose   you   also  have  the  18.1  production  release  in
                /tools/innovus.18.10.  Find the .info files to compare:

                >ls /tools/innovus18.10/share/innovus/version_info

                innovus.18.10-p006_1.cui.info  innovus.18.10-p006_1.info

                >ls /tools/innovus18.11/share/innovus/version_info

                innovus.18.11-s080_1.cui.info  innovus.18.11-s080_1.info

                Then, run the compare_release command to  compare  either  the
                legacy (.info.) or Common UI versions (.cui.info):

                innovus> compare_release \

                -base_file  /tools/innovus18.10/share/innovus/version_info/in-
                novus.18.10-p006_1.info \

                -target_file            /tools/innovus18.11/share/innovus/ver-
                sion_info/innovus.18.11-s080_1.info \

                -out_file 18.11.diff

                The  output file will show all the differences between the two
                releases.

